SIMPLE: muscovite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muscovite
<hw>Mus"co*vite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Muscovy
glass</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or inhabitant of Muscovy or
ancient Russia; hence, a Russian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An inhabitant of Moscow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Common potash mica, essentially
<chform>KAl3Si3O10(OH)2</chform>. It is used as an electrical insulator.
See <er>Mica</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscovy duck</ent>⟦br⟧
